    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Add missing get_drb() function implementation\n\n### Summary\nUsers attempting to call `get_drb()` were experiencing unexpected behavior because the function was not implemented in the codebase. This change adds the missing implementation along with proper validation and error handling.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB_radio_bearers.c`: Added `get_drb()` function implementation with proper DRB ID validation and active state checking\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB_radio_bearers.h`: Added function declaration\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB_radio_bearers.c`: Added missing include for assertions\n\n### Reproduction\nPrior to this fix, attempting to call `get_drb()` would result in compilation errors or linker errors since the function was referenced but not implemented. After this change, users can successfully call `get_drb(ue, drb_id)` to retrieve a pointer to the DRB structure, or NULL if the DRB is inactive or invalid.\n\nThe function properly validates DRB IDs are within the valid range (1-32) and checks the DRB active state before returning a pointer to the DRB structure, consistent with existing code patterns in the RRC radio bearers module.\n"
}